text: William Hoskins may refer to: * William Hoskins (MP) for Westbury in 1555 * William Lawrence Hoskins (1828–1901), American politician * William Hoskins (inventor) (1862–1934), American co-inventor of nichrome and modern billiard chalk * William George Hoskins (1908–1992), English local historian, academic and author * William Hoskins (baseball) (1914–1975), American Negro league baseball player * Will Hoskins (born 1986), English association football striker ==See also== *William Hosking, writer and architect
